    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>The teeth of a shark, which is any fish of the order Selachii. Sharks continually shed and replace their teeth during life, thus some may shed up to 35,000 teeth in a lifetime.</Note_Text>
